Package us.ihmc.euclid.referenceFrame.interfaces

Interface FixedFrameTuple4DBasics

  • All Superinterfaces:
    us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Clearable, FrameTuple4DReadOnly, ReferenceFrameHolder, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Transformable, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple4D.interfaces.Tuple4DBasics, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple4D.interfaces.Tuple4DReadOnly
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    FixedFrameQuaternionBasics, FixedFrameVector4DBasics, FrameQuaternionBasics, FrameTuple4DBasics, FrameVector4DBasics
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FrameQuaternion, FrameVector4D
    public interface FixedFrameTuple4DBasics
extends FrameTuple4DReadOnly, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple4D.interfaces.Tuple4DBasics
    FixedFrameTuple4DBasics is the base implementation for FrameQuaternion and FrameVector4D.

    In addition to representing a Tuple4DBasics, a constant ReferenceFrame is associated to a FixedFrameTuple4DBasics. This allows, for instance, to enforce, at runtime, that operations on tuples occur in the same coordinate system.

    When using this interface, the reference frame of this tuple is assumed to be immutable, i.e. the tuple is always expressed in the same reference frame.

    Because a FixedFrameTuple4DBasics extends Tuple4DBasics, it is compatible with methods only requiring Tuple4DBasics. However, these methods do NOT assert that the operation occur in the proper coordinate system. Use this feature carefully and always prefer using methods requiring FixedFrameTuple4DBasics.

      • setMatchingFrame

        default void setMatchingFrame​(FrameTuple4DReadOnly other)
        Sets this frame tuple to other.

        If other is expressed in the frame as this, then this method is equivalent to set(FrameTuple4DReadOnly).

        If other is expressed in a different frame than this, then this is set to other and then transformed to be expressed in this.getReferenceFrame().

        Parameters:
        other - the other tuple to copy the values from. Not modified.
